navigationText.en: Silver provides far better performance for a number of applications than either of its two components on their own

text.en: Silver is a synthetic fiber comprising a blend of Danline and Polyester. Polyester is a sinking fiber with density of 1.38 and adds extra tensile strength. Danline is a buoant fiber with density 0.91 that contributes additional abrasion resistance compared with pure Polyester, The combination of the two gives a slightly negatively buoyant rope offering the best of both worlds in terms of tensile strenght and abrasion resistance.

Fiskevegn's twisting department blends Danline and Polyester fiber to its famous Silver yarn, which allows for an ideal all round fishing rope.

Silver provides far better performance for a number of applications than either of its two components on their own. We use Silver especially in our longline rope and end ropes

children.text: Welcome to our new portfolio!
What just happened?

We have just added a new repository to our GitHub account. There we have all the code for this portfolio’s frontend made with Gatsby, and Sanity Studio, the environment where we will be editing our content. They are deployed on Netlify. So everything is ready for us to get started with our portfolio! We can even edit content and use the Netlify widget on the Studio’s dashboard to deploy new changes to the web.
Sanity.io lets us work with structured content. That means we can add more content types. Who knows, We might add a blog,
maybe a podcast
some products that we need to market
, or our bi-weekly newsletter (we should really get on that soon)! We can even connect other frontends, or apps, to our Sanity project. Who knows, one day we can even try
one of those voice assistants
with it?
But firstly, how could we customize this portfolio to our own branding and such?

We should probably check out the tutorial videos on how to get started with customizing both the content schema and the frontend accordingly. We're sure that we'll find them on the dashboard in the Studio.
There's plenty of cool things to explore:
How to customize content schemas
How to use structure builder to make  own workflows
How to manage widgets on  dashboard
How to turn on real-time content preview in Gatsby
And if we're stuck, we could always seek answers in
the friendly developer community
Hurray! We now have a portfolio powered by Gatsby and Sanity.io.

In doing so we collaborate with scientists and industry partners around the world. We have a range of material and equipment that can serve as valuable contributions to marine R&D projects.

text.en: Fiskevegn anticipates that successful development of one viable solution one may require generation and testing of a multitude of ideas. Our current projects range from automation of manufacturing via development of new fishing methods such as the deepwater tornado trolling system, to a long-term commitment to develop environment-friendly synthetic bait to replace consumable food as bait.

navigationText.en: Particularly suitable for ropes that have to withstand demanding conditions, not least in the fishing industry

text.en: Danline (also called Polysteel) was originally developed in Japan to meet the need for a stronger and more durable polypropylene based fiber. This is achieved through a mix of polypropylene and polyetylene. Fiskevegn set up the first Danline extruders in Europe in the 1980s and still manufactures its own high quality fiber.

Its strength and good abrasion resistance make Danline particularly suitable for ropes that have to withstand demanding conditions, not least in the fishing industry. This material does not rot or absorb water, withstands most acids, alkalis, is stabilized against sunlight and floats due to a specific weight of only 0,91.

navigationText.en: Our solutions are in use from coastal dinghies in Greenland to ocean-going vessels of 70 meters in Antarctica

text.en: Development of a successful fishery is complex. Singular focus on efficient capture is often counterproductive by resulting in large volumes of low-value seafood. The value chain from capture to consumption needs to be developed. Fiskevegn works with private operators, scientists and public agencies to realize maximum seafood value whilst reducing efforts and environmental impacts.
text.no: I Fiskevegn har vi bred kunnskap og erfaring med utvikling av fiskeri i mange land, f.eks. Australia. Vi tenker helhetlig med samfunnsøkonomi, miljø og ressurser i fokus, og tilpasser fartøy, teknologi, utstyr og metoder til dette. I helhetstenkningen inngår også vurdering eierskap, flåtestruktur, verdikjedestruktur, markeder og markedsføring.

text.en: Our position in fishery development is as a specialist on low-impact, fuel-efficient fisheries that deliver seafood of high value. Many fisheries have great potential to move away from low-value to high-value seafood harvesting, and doing the environment a favor while doing so.

text.en: Life at Fiskevegn entails many exciting challenges and a hectic and good working environment. We are a growing company founded on strong environmental values and are focussed on innovation driven by equal doses of science and experience. Interested applicants may contact our Head of Office.
text.no: Som en bedrift i et voksende marked er vi hele tiden på utkikk etter de rette medarbeiderne. Vi kan love deg mange spennende utfordringer og et hektisk og godt arbeidsmiljø.

text.en: Since its inception Fiskevegn has built on the core values of quality, delivery and innovation. Our core values have yielded results for both our customer and for us.
text.no: Bedriften startet i det små på den vesle øya Barmen på nøyaktig 62 grader nord i 1968. Siden 1973 har AS Fiskevegn holdt til på Flatraket i Selje kommune, med Stadhavet som nærmeste nabo. Mange av våre ansatte har lang erfaring fra arbeid om bord i fiskebåter, både i innland og utland.

text.en: Fiskevegn is a leading international manufacturer and supplier of fiber, rope, fishing systems for automatic longlining, fishing gears and supplies for crew and vessels. We are proud to be one of the most trusted names in the global arena of longline fishing.
text.no: Som totalleverandør til autoline- og garnflåten yter vi også veiledning, råd og service innen område som prosjektutvikling og fiskeriutvikling over hele verden. Vi leverer også utstyr til havbruk og offshore. Kombinasjonen av bransjeerfaring, målrettet produktutvikling, god markedskunnskap og dyp forankring i det norske og internasjonale fiskerimiljøet – gjør Fiskevegn til en god samarbeidspartner.

title.no: En sentral aktør på den globale arena for linefiske

text.en: Fiskevegn is working together with mulitple industry operators, goverments and NGO's to eliminate IUU fishing and to drive for economically viable, sustainable solutions towards safer, cleaner oceans. We are also a member of several industry associations to keep current with new developments in manufacturing technology.
text.no: Fiskevegn jobber i dag med flere industriaktører, myndigheter og NGOer for å eliminere ulovlig fiskeri og jobber for økonomisk levedyktige og bærekraftige løsninger mot tryggere, renere hav.

text.en: Our main office is located at beautiful Flatraket, at the west coast of Norway
text.no: Vårt hovedkontor er lokalisert på nydelige Flatraket, på Vestlandet.

text.en: In all Fiskevegn's activity sectors, industry know-how, on-the-fly problem-solving skills and a high level of service is essential. We strive to provide excellent service and rewarding collaborations for our customers, suppliers and many research- and industry partners.
text.no: For oss i Fiskevegn er det viktig å følge opp kundene våre. Vi yter allsidig service og en rekke tjenester, fra garnmontering, service og ettersyn av autolineanlegg – til prosjektplanlegging og fiskeriutvikling i stor skala.

title.no: Allsidig service og en rekke tjenester

text.en: Modern fishing, aquaculture and a wide range of maritime acitivities require quality products, preventive maintenance, and a supporting infrastructure that works.

title.en: Fiskevegn supplies business-essential products and services

text.en: Fiskevegn is a leading international manufacturer and supplier of fiber, rope, fishing systems for automatic longlining, fishing gears and supplies for crew and vessels. We support vessel projects from idea to realization and can offer advice on everything from suitable shipyards, suppliers, alliance partners and how best to achieve optimal solutions for your vessel.
text.no: Vi er totalleverandør til garn- og lineflåten. Vi tilbyr alt fra automatiske linesystemer, fiskeredskaper og utstyr til mannskap og fartøy. Kombinasjonen av bransjeerfaring, målrettet produktutvikling, god markedskunnskap og dyp forankring i det norske og internasjonale fiskerimiljøet - gjør Fiskevegn til en god samarbeidspartner.

text.en: Fiskevegn supplies business-essential products and services. Supplying the ocean-going fishing fleet in particular can be compared to servicing the airline industry. Many ocean-going fishing vessels barely touch base before returning back to sea. Also for coastal vessels, the reality is that if essensial equipment breaks down or gears are lost, there may be no choice but to return to port while losing time and revenues.
text.no: For oss i Fiskevegn er det viktig å følge opp kundene våre. Vi yter allsidig service og en rekke tjenester, fra garnmontering, service og ettersyn av autolineanlegg – til prosjektplanlegging og fiskeriutvikling i stor skala.
